msgid "Using PGP with Git"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:88 4b3f683db00445d8ab6099dd6d0c7a99
msgid ""
"If you’re submitting a patch via GitHub (or a similar Git server), please"
" sign your Git commits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:90 2dc4d193a77b4fbe8e957e476cba12e9
msgid "Set up Git to use your key:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:98 e91562a18e774194bff4dea9cb579ec4
msgid "Set up Git to sign your commits with your key:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:105 eef2aebbfb414375a415235285577152
msgid "Alternatively, manually specify when a commit is to be signed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:113 6839f7a8fe3b49fc978f302884815c6a
msgid ""
"(Optional) Create signed tags. Signed commits are totally sufficient to "
"contribute to Qubes OS. However, if you have commits which are not signed"
" and you do not want to change them, you can create a signed tag for the "
"commit and push it before the check."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:115 7029250670a942e19b9a1ed64870ba68
msgid ""
"This is useful for example, if you have a commit back in the git history "
"which you like to sign now without rewriting the history."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:122 6b536ee8733442fdbd2180888a261302
msgid ""
"You can also create an alias to make this easier. Edit your "
"``~/.gitconfig`` file. In the ``[alias]`` section, add ``stag`` to create"
" signed tags and ``spush`` to create signed tags and push them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:131 e990185d713b403a8f8a82692bfd2521
msgid ""
"You may also find it convenient to have an alias for verifying the tag on"
" the latest commit:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:142 bd41cdd8eb3241c784086a6b8905ac35
msgid "GitHub Signature Verification (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:145 e54392cf93d94f9cb20d0c62f7d8580a
msgid ""
"GitHub shows a green ``Verified`` label indicating that the GPG signature"
" could be verified using any of the contributor’s GPG keys uploaded to "
"GitHub. You can upload your public key on GitHub by adding your public "
"GPG key on the `New GPG key <https://github.com/settings/gpg/new>`__ "
"under the `SSH GPG keys page <https://github.com/settings/keys>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:148 8be494a6185e42c2bb15f96fccc396be
msgid "Code Signature Checks"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:151 57c597feced04d7cafbb2d04484c6e68
msgid ""
"The `signature-checker <https://github.com/marmarek/signature-checker>`__"
" checks if code contributions are signed. Although GitHub adds a little "
"green ``Verified`` button next to the commit, the `signature-checker "
"<https://github.com/marmarek/signature-checker>`__ uses this algorithm to"
" check if a commit is correctly signed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:153 61a563463160478cadfd93aeb5d12aa8
msgid "Is the commit signed? If the commit is not signed, you can see the message"
msgstr ""

