msgid "No Signature Found"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:169 63bc186736824d01b8704a8d30d5bbda
msgid "In this case, you have several options to sign the commit:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:171 22a1b5ee5ddc4573858d05df3f889442
msgid ""
"Amend the commit and replace it with a signed commit. You can use this "
"command to create a new signed commit:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:178 dd3eae274e8544eebaa89129e0bcd45a
msgid "This also rewrites the commit so you need to push it forcefully:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:186 c5f18974fa884b058f9c6ea5964053f3
msgid ""
"Create a signed tag for the unsigned commit. If the commit is back in "
"history and you do not want to change it, you can create a signed tag for"
" this commit and push the signature. You can use the alias from above:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:194 d682fc597d2842c6ac5288331bdc7ec8
msgid ""
"Now, the signature checker needs to re-check the signature. Please "
"comment on the pull request that you would like to have the signatures "
"checked again."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:199 8da37f11a587495fa4a51a20f49520c9
msgid "Unable To Verify"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:204 c83ab5bff2e5464ca02cf7ba3f90a68d
msgid ""
"This means that the `signature-checker <https://github.com/marmarek"
"/signature-checker>`__ has found a signature for the commit but is not "
"able to verify it using the any key available. This might be that you "
"forgot to upload the key to a key server. Please upload it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:207 8a7b906c077e4304829c73c81e87cba8
msgid "Using PGP with Email"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/code/code-signing.rst:210 5a5db001e4c74ef8801bf951e3fccbdc
msgid ""
"If you’re submitting a patch by emailing the :ref:`developer mailing list"
" <introduction/support:qubes-devel>`, simply sign your email with your "
"PGP key. One good way to do this is with a program like `Enigmail "
"<https://www.enigmail.net/>`__. Enigmail is a security addon for the "
"Mozilla Thunderbird email client that allows you to easily digitally "
"encrypt and sign your emails."
msgstr ""

